NAME
    Catalyst::Plugin::Session::Store::Memcached - Memcached session storage
    backend.

SYNOPSIS
        use Catalyst qw/Session Session::Store::Memcached Session::State::Foo/;
    
        MyApp->config->{session} = {
            expires => 3600,
            servers => '127.0.0.1:11210',
        };

        # ... in an action:
        $c->session->{foo} = 'bar'; # will be saved

DESCRIPTION
    "Catalyst::Plugin::Session::Store::Memcached" is a fast session storage
    plugin for Catalyst that uses memcached cache. It is based on
    Cache::Memcached::Fast.

  METHODS
    get_session_data
    store_session_data
    delete_session_data
    delete_expired_sessions
        These are implementations of the required methods for a store. See
        Catalyst::Plugin::Session::Store.

    get_and_set_session_data
        This is the optional method for atomic write semantics. See
        Catalyst::Plugin::Session::AtomicWrite.

    setup_session
        Sets up the session connection.

CAVEATS
CONFIGURATION
SEE ALSO
    Catalyst, Catalyst::Plugin::Session, Cache::Memcached::Fast.

